    "culture": {
      "vibe": "New York City campus culture \u2014 fast-paced, ambitious, diverse, and never dull. Queens is genuine NYC \u2014 the most ethnically diverse urban county in the world. Campus itself is a green oasis but step outside and you're in one of the world's great cities.",
      "thingsToDo": "Central Park, Manhattan skyline, Brooklyn Bridge, NYCFC/Red Bulls soccer, MSG events, Broadway, Museum Mile, Queens food scene (most diverse cuisine on earth), Citi Field, every type of music venue imaginable. NYC needs no introduction.",
      "socialScene": "Extremely diverse student body. Every culture represented. Catholic university ethos but applied liberally. Commuter culture means less tight-knit than residential campuses. City is the campus in many ways.",
      "olivierMatch": "\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605 NYC is incomparable for urban experience. Weather is cold (winters) which is the main lifestyle mismatch. If Olivier can handle cold winters, the city culture and clinical network are extraordinary.",
      "lifestyleTags": "NYC energy, global, never boring"
    },
    "facilityDetails": {
      "stadium": "Belson Stadium \u2014 3,000 capacity, FieldTurf surface, lights, permanent seating. Located in Queens, adjacent to the main St. John's campus. Big East broadcast-ready.",
      "trainingFields": "2 practice fields at Belson complex. St. John's Athletics also uses Lou Carnesecca Arena outdoor areas for overflow training. Limited by NYC land constraints but well-maintained.",
      "strengthConditioning": "St. John's Carnesecca Arena Athletic Weight Room \u2014 12,000 sq ft, full free weight section, cable systems, functional training area. Dedicated performance coach for soccer. Recovery suite with normatec boots and contrast bath access through athletic training room.",
      "sportsScience": "GPS tracking (Statsports) for all sessions. Video analysis via Hudl. Department of Human Performance and Exercise Science has biomechanics teaching lab and exercise physiology lab.",
      "sportsMed": "Dedicated certified athletic trainer. Hospital for Special Surgery (HSS \u2014 ranked #1 orthopaedic hospital in the world, 14 consecutive years) has a partnership with St. John's Athletics. NYU Langone Sports Performance Center and NY Presbyterian Hospital are both accessible. Best sports medicine access of any school in this guide from a graduate school observation perspective.",
      "academicLabs": "St. John's School of Education Human Performance: exercise physiology lab, anatomy lab, biomechanics teaching space. NYC clinical placement network is extraordinary \u2014 students can access HSS, NYU Langone, and NY Presbyterian for DPT observation hours without leaving the city.",
      "extras": "Barclays Center and Madison Square Garden \u2014 two of the world's great arenas within 30 minutes. NYCFC and NY Red Bulls training ground access for players with agent connections. NYC's unmatched cultural offering: every museum, park, restaurant, and music venue. Metropolitan Museum of Art, Central Park, Brooklyn Bridge all accessible by subway.",
      "rating": "Good",
      "note": "Belson Stadium and the athletic facilities are functional but not elite by D1 standards. The extraordinary differentiator is the NYC clinical network \u2014 Hospital for Special Surgery is the #1 orthopaedic hospital in the world and St. John's players can access it for clinical observation."
    },
